msgstr ""
"**Nota**: Le app che usano `fetch()` o altre API della piattaforma web che "
"dipendono da un'origine reale devono essere servite tramite HTTP (gli URL "
"file:// incorrono in errori CORS / \"Failed to fetch\"). Qualsiasi server "
"statico locale è sufficiente:"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:31
msgid ""
"The `perry-codegen-wasm` crate compiles HIR directly to WASM bytecode using "
"`wasm-encoder`. The output WASM:"
msgstr ""
"Il crate `perry-codegen-wasm` compila l'HIR direttamente in bytecode WASM "
"usando `wasm-encoder`. Il WASM prodotto:"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:33
msgid ""
"Imports ~280 host functions under the `rt` namespace (string ops, math, "
"console, JSON, classes, closures, promises, fetch, etc.)"
msgstr ""
"Importa circa 280 funzioni host nel namespace `rt` (operazioni sulle "
"stringhe, matematica, console, JSON, classi, closure, promise, fetch, ecc.)"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:34
msgid "Imports user-declared FFI functions under the `ffi` namespace"
msgstr "Importa le funzioni FFI dichiarate dall'utente nel namespace `ffi`"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:35
msgid ""
"Exports `_start`, `memory`, `__indirect_function_table`, and every user "
"function as `__wasm_func_<idx>` (so async function bodies compiled to JS can"
" call back into WASM)"
msgstr ""
"Esporta `_start`, `memory`, `__indirect_function_table` e ogni funzione "
"utente come `__wasm_func_<idx>` (in modo che i corpi delle funzioni async "
"compilati in JS possano richiamare il WASM)"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:37
msgid ""
"The NaN-boxing scheme matches the native `perry-runtime` — f64 values with "
"STRING_TAG/POINTER_TAG/INT32_TAG — so the same value representation is used "
"across native and WASM targets. The JS bridge wraps every host import with "
"bit-level reinterpretation so f64 NaN-boxed values pass through the BigInt-"
"based JS↔WASM i64 boundary intact (BigInt(NaN) would otherwise throw)."
msgstr ""
"Lo schema NaN-boxing corrisponde al `perry-runtime` nativo — valori f64 con "
"STRING_TAG/POINTER_TAG/INT32_TAG — in modo che la stessa rappresentazione "
"dei valori sia usata tra i target native e WASM. Il bridge JS avvolge ogni "
"import host con una reinterpretazione a livello di bit in modo che i valori "
"NaN-boxed f64 attraversino intatti il confine i64 JS↔WASM basato su BigInt "
"(altrimenti `BigInt(NaN)` genererebbe un'eccezione)."

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:41
msgid ""
"**Full TypeScript language**: classes (with constructors, methods, "
"getters/setters, inheritance, fields), async/await, closures (with "
"captures), generators, destructuring, template literals, generics, enums, "
"try/catch/finally"
msgstr ""
"**Linguaggio TypeScript completo**: classi (con costruttori, metodi, "
"getter/setter, ereditarietà, campi), async/await, closure (con cattura di "
"variabili), generatori, destrutturazione, template literal, generici, enum, "
"try/catch/finally"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:42
msgid ""
"**Module system**: cross-module imports, top-level `const`/`let` (promoted "
"to WASM globals), circular imports"
msgstr ""
"**Sistema di moduli**: import cross-module, `const`/`let` a livello "
"superiore (promossi a globali WASM), import circolari"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:43
msgid ""
"**Standard library**: String/Array/Object methods, Map/Set, JSON, Date, "
"RegExp, Math, Error, URL/URLSearchParams, Buffer, Promise (with "
"`.then`/`.catch`/`.allSettled`/`.race`/`.any`/`.all`)"
msgstr ""
"**Libreria standard**: metodi String/Array/Object, Map/Set, JSON, Date, "
"RegExp, Math, Error, URL/URLSearchParams, Buffer, Promise (con "
"`.then`/`.catch`/`.allSettled`/`.race`/`.any`/`.all`)"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:44
msgid ""
"**Async**: `async`/`await` (compiled to JS Promises), "
"`setTimeout`/`setInterval`, `fetch()` with full request options (method, "
"headers, body)"
msgstr ""
"**Async**: `async`/`await` (compilati in Promise JS), "
"`setTimeout`/`setInterval`, `fetch()` con opzioni di richiesta complete "
"(method, headers, body)"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:45
msgid ""
"**Threading**: `perry/thread` `parallelMap`/`parallelFilter`/`spawn` via Web"
" Worker pool with one WASM instance per worker (see "
"[Threading](../threading/overview.md))"
msgstr ""
"**Threading**: `perry/thread` `parallelMap`/`parallelFilter`/`spawn` tramite"
" pool di Web Worker con un'istanza WASM per worker (vedi "
"[Threading](../threading/overview.md))"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:46
msgid ""
"**DOM-based UI**: every widget in `perry/ui` (`VStack`, `HStack`, `ZStack`, "
"`Text`, `Button`, `TextField`, `Toggle`, `Slider`, `ScrollView`, `Picker`, "
"`Image`, `Canvas`, `Form`, `Section`, `NavigationStack`, `Table`, "
"`LazyVStack`, `TextArea`, etc.) maps to a DOM element with flexbox layout. "
"State bindings (`bindText`/`bindSlider`/`bindToggle`/`bindForEach`/...) work"
" via reactive subscribers."
msgstr ""
"**UI basata su DOM**: ogni widget in `perry/ui` (`VStack`, `HStack`, "
"`ZStack`, `Text`, `Button`, `TextField`, `Toggle`, `Slider`, `ScrollView`, "
"`Picker`, `Image`, `Canvas`, `Form`, `Section`, `NavigationStack`, `Table`, "
"`LazyVStack`, `TextArea`, ecc.) è mappato a un elemento DOM con layout "
"flexbox. I binding di stato "
"(`bindText`/`bindSlider`/`bindToggle`/`bindForEach`/...) funzionano tramite "
"subscriber reattivi."

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:47
msgid ""
"**System APIs**: `localStorage`\\-backed preferences/keychain, dark mode "
"detection (`prefers-color-scheme`), Web Notifications, clipboard, file "
"open/save dialogs, File System Access API, Web Audio capture"
msgstr ""
"**API di sistema**: preferenze/portachiavi basati su `localStorage`, "
"rilevamento modalità scura (`prefers-color-scheme`), Web Notifications, "
"appunti, finestre di dialogo per apertura/salvataggio file, File System "
"Access API, acquisizione Web Audio"

