"// Read directory contents\n"
"const files = readdirSync(scratch)\n"
"for (const file of files) {\n"
"    console.log(file)\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"// Remove an empty directory\n"
"rmdirSync(outDir)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:58
msgid ""
"For recursive removal Perry exposes `rmRecursive` (a thin wrapper around "
"`std::fs::remove_dir_all`). Wired via "
"[\\#193](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/193) through "
"`js_fs_rm_recursive` in the LLVM backend."
msgstr ""
"Per la rimozione ricorsiva Perry espone `rmRecursive` (un wrapper sottile "
"attorno a `std::fs::remove_dir_all`). Collegato tramite "
"[\\#193](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/193) attraverso "
"`js_fs_rm_recursive` nel backend LLVM."

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:63
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { rmRecursive } from \"fs\";\n"
"rmRecursive(\"output\"); // Recursive remove; returns 1 on success, 0 on failure.\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:68
msgid "Path Utilities"
msgstr "Utility per i path"

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:70
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"const dir = dirname(configPath)\n"
"const cfgPath = join(dir, \"config.json\")\n"
"const name = basename(cfgPath)        // \"config.json\"\n"
"const abs = resolve(\"relative/path\")  // Absolute path\n"
"console.log(`${name} ${abs.length > 0}`)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:78
msgid ""
"For `import.meta.url` → filesystem path conversion, use `fileURLToPath` from"
" the `url` module:"
msgstr ""
"Per la conversione da `import.meta.url` a path del file system, usare "
"`fileURLToPath` dal modulo `url`:"

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:81
msgid ""
"```text\n"
"import { fileURLToPath } from \"url\";\n"
"import { dirname } from \"path\";\n"
"\n"
"const dir = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:90
msgid ""
"`fs` numeric file descriptors and `fs.promises.FileHandle` objects are "
"thread-affine across `perry/thread`. Passing a numeric fd into `spawn` or "
"`parallelMap` copies only the number; the receiving thread has its own fd "
"registry, so operations fail with `EBADF`. Passing a `FileHandle` produces a"
" detached handle with `fd === -1`."
msgstr ""
"I descrittori di file numerici di `fs` e gli oggetti "
"`fs.promises.FileHandle` sono thread-affine attraverso `perry/thread`. "
"Passare un fd numerico a `spawn` o `parallelMap` copia solo il numero; il "
"thread ricevente ha il proprio registro fd, quindi le operazioni falliscono "
"con `EBADF`. Passare un `FileHandle` produce un handle distaccato con `fd "
"=== -1`."

#: src/stdlib/fs.md:96
msgid ""
"Pass file paths across thread boundaries and reopen files inside the worker."
msgstr ""
"Passa i path dei file attraverso i confini dei thread e riapri i file "
"all'interno del worker."

