msgid ""
"The canonical \"deploy a hono app as a native binary on a Linux VM\" pattern"
" compiles and links on a stock Perry binary. A hand-rolled `node:http` "
"adapter that drives `app.fetch` works directly:"
msgstr ""
"Il pattern canonico \"distribuire un'app Hono come binario nativo su una VM "
"Linux\" viene compilato e collegato su un binario Perry standard. Un adapter"
" `node:http` scritto a mano che guida `app.fetch` funziona direttamente:"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:198
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { createServer } from \"node:http\";\n"
"\n"
"const server = createServer((req, res) => {\n"
"  const headers = new Headers();\n"
"  headers.set(\"content-type\", \"text/plain\");\n"
"  const fetchReq = new Request(`http://localhost${req.url}`, { method: req.method });\n"
"  // ... await app.fetch(fetchReq), then copy status/headers/body onto `res`.\n"
"  res.end(\"ok\");\n"
"});\n"
"server.listen(3000);\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/http.md:211
msgid ""
"The `node:http` server FFIs and the Web Fetch `Headers` / `Request` / "
"`Response` constructors now link together (issues #589, #1652). For a "
"turnkey adapter, prefer [perry's Fastify binding](#fastify-server) with a "
"single catch-all route delegating to `app.fetch`."
msgstr ""
"Le FFI del server `node:http` e i costruttori Web Fetch `Headers` / "
"`Request` / `Response` sono ora collegati tra loro (issue #589, #1652). Per "
"un adattatore pronto all'uso, preferire il [binding Fastify di "
"perry](#fastify-server) con un'unica route catch-all che delega a "
"`app.fetch`."

#: src/stdlib/http.md:216
msgid "`@perryts/hono-server`"
msgstr "`@perryts/hono-server`"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:218
msgid ""
"`@perryts/hono-server` (in-tree at `packages/hono-perry-server`) packages "
"that catch-all-over-Fastify shim as Hono's standard `serve({ fetch, port })`"
" contract — the Perry counterpart to `@hono/node-server` / `@hono/bun`:"
msgstr ""
"`@perryts/hono-server` (incluso nel repository in `packages/hono-perry-"
"server`) impacchetta quello shim catch-all-su-Fastify come contratto "
"standard `serve({ fetch, port })` di Hono — il corrispettivo Perry di "
"`@hono/node-server` / `@hono/bun`:"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:222
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { Hono } from \"hono\"\n"
"import { serve } from \"@perryts/hono-server\"\n"
"\n"
"const app = new Hono()\n"
"app.get(\"/\", (c) => c.json({ ok: true }))\n"
"\n"
"serve({ fetch: app.fetch, port: 3000 }, (info) => {\n"
"  console.log(`listening on :${info.port}`)\n"
"})\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/http.md:234
msgid ""
"It translates each Fastify request into a Web `Request`, awaits `app.fetch`,"
" and copies the `Response`'s status / headers / body back onto the reply. "
"Requires Perry ≥ 0.5.1027 (`Request.headers`, #1649). Tracked at #1654."
msgstr ""
"Traduce ogni richiesta Fastify in una `Request` Web, attende `app.fetch` e "
"copia lo status / gli header / il body della `Response` nella risposta. "
"Richiede Perry ≥ 0.5.1027 (`Request.headers`, #1649). Tracciato al #1654."

#: src/stdlib/http.md:238
msgid "Fastify Server"
msgstr "Server Fastify"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:240
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import fastify from \"fastify\"\n"
"\n"
"const app = fastify()\n"
"\n"
"app.get(\"/\", async (request: any, reply: any) => {\n"
"    return { hello: \"world\" }\n"
"})\n"
"\n"
"app.get(\"/users/:id\", async (request: any, reply: any) => {\n"
"    const id = request.params.id\n"
"    return { id, name: \"User \" + id }\n"
"})\n"
"\n"
"app.post(\"/data\", async (request: any, reply: any) => {\n"
"    const body = request.body\n"
"    reply.code(201)\n"
"    return { received: body }\n"
"})\n"
"\n"
"app.listen({ port: 3000 }, () => {\n"
"    console.log(\"Server running on port 3000\")\n"
"})\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/http.md:265
msgid ""
"Perry's Fastify implementation is API-compatible with the npm package. "
"Routes, request/reply objects, params, query strings, and JSON body parsing "
"all work."
msgstr ""
"L'implementazione Fastify di Perry è compatibile a livello API con il "
"pacchetto npm. Route, oggetti request/reply, parametri, query string e "
"parsing del body JSON funzionano tutti correttamente."

