#: src/stdlib/other.md:60
msgid "Native bindings via `perry-ext-zlib` (v0.5.541)."
msgstr "Binding nativi tramite `perry-ext-zlib` (v0.5.541)."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:62
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import zlib from \"zlib\";\n"
"\n"
"const compressed = zlib.gzipSync(\"Hello, World!\");\n"
"const decompressed = zlib.gunzipSync(compressed);\n"
"console.log(decompressed.toString()); // \"Hello, World!\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:70
msgid "cron / node-cron (Job Scheduling)"
msgstr "cron / node-cron (Pianificazione di job)"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:72
msgid ""
"Native bindings via `perry-ext-cron` (v0.5.564). Both `cron` and `node-cron`"
" package names route to the same backend."
msgstr ""
"Binding nativi tramite `perry-ext-cron` (v0.5.564). Sia il nome del "
"pacchetto `cron` che `node-cron` vengono instradati allo stesso backend."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:75
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { CronJob } from \"cron\";\n"
"\n"
"const job = new CronJob(\"*/5 * * * *\", () => {\n"
"  console.log(\"Runs every 5 minutes\");\n"
"});\n"
"job.start();\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:84
msgid "ethers (Ethereum)"
msgstr "ethers (Ethereum)"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:86
msgid ""
"Native bindings via `perry-ext-ethers` (v0.5.556) — backed by [`ethers-"
"rs`](https://github.com/gakonst/ethers-rs)\\-style ABI plumbing through "
"`perry-ffi`'s BigInt + Buffer surfaces."
msgstr ""
"Binding nativi tramite `perry-ext-ethers` (v0.5.556) — supportato "
"dall'infrastruttura ABI in stile [`ethers-"
"rs`](https://github.com/gakonst/ethers-rs) attraverso le superfici BigInt + "
"Buffer di `perry-ffi`."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:90
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { ethers } from \"ethers\";\n"
"\n"
"const wallet = ethers.Wallet.createRandom();\n"
"console.log(\"address:\", wallet.address);\n"
"console.log(\"private key:\", wallet.privateKey);\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:98
msgid "events (EventEmitter)"
msgstr "events (EventEmitter)"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:100
msgid ""
"Native bindings via `perry-ext-events` (v0.5.546). The `EventEmitter` shape "
"matches Node.js — `on`, `off`, `once`, `emit`, `removeAllListeners`."
msgstr ""
"Binding nativi tramite `perry-ext-events` (v0.5.546). La struttura di "
"`EventEmitter` corrisponde a quella di Node.js — `on`, `off`, `once`, "
"`emit`, `removeAllListeners`."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:103
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { EventEmitter } from \"events\";\n"
"\n"
"const ee = new EventEmitter();\n"
"ee.on(\"data\", (chunk) => console.log(\"got:\", chunk));\n"
"ee.emit(\"data\", \"hello\");\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:111
msgid "exponential-backoff (Retry Logic)"
msgstr "exponential-backoff (Logica di retry)"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:113
msgid "Native bindings via `perry-ext-exponential-backoff` (v0.5.542)."
msgstr "Binding nativi tramite `perry-ext-exponential-backoff` (v0.5.542)."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:115
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { backOff } from \"exponential-backoff\";\n"
"\n"
"const result = await backOff(() => fetchUnstableEndpoint(), {\n"
"  numOfAttempts: 5,\n"
"  startingDelay: 200,\n"
"  timeMultiple: 2,\n"
"});\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:125
msgid "decimal.js / bignumber.js (Arbitrary Precision)"
msgstr "decimal.js / bignumber.js (Precisione arbitraria)"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:127
msgid ""
"Native bindings via `perry-ext-decimal` (v0.5.547). Both package names route"
" to the same backend — `Decimal` and `BigNumber` are both exposed."
msgstr ""
"Binding nativi tramite `perry-ext-decimal` (v0.5.547). Entrambi i nomi di "
"pacchetto vengono instradati allo stesso backend — sia `Decimal` che "
"`BigNumber` sono esposti."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:130
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import Decimal from \"decimal.js\"\n"
"\n"
"function decimalExample(): void {\n"
"    const a = new Decimal(\"0.1\")\n"
"    const b = new Decimal(\"0.2\")\n"
"    const sum = a.plus(b) // Exactly 0.3 (no floating point errors)\n"
"\n"
"    console.log(sum.toFixed(2))      // \"0.30\"\n"
"    console.log(sum.toNumber())      // 0.3\n"
"    console.log(a.times(b).toFixed(2)) // \"0.02\"\n"
"    console.log(a.div(b).toFixed(1))   // \"0.5\"\n"
"    console.log(a.pow(10).toString())  // 1e-10\n"
"    console.log(a.sqrt().toFixed(3))   // \"0.316\"\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:147
msgid "dayjs / date-fns (Date Manipulation)"
msgstr "dayjs / date-fns (Manipolazione delle date)"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:149
msgid ""
"Native bindings via `perry-ext-dayjs` (v0.5.548). Both package names route "
"to the same Rust backend — same parse/format/diff surface."
msgstr ""
"Binding nativi tramite `perry-ext-dayjs` (v0.5.548). Entrambi i nomi di "
"pacchetto vengono instradati allo stesso backend Rust — stessa superficie di"
" parse/format/diff."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:152
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import dayjs from \"dayjs\";\n"
"\n"
"const now = dayjs();\n"
"const tomorrow = now.add(1, \"day\");\n"
"console.log(tomorrow.format(\"YYYY-MM-DD\"));\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:160
msgid "moment (Legacy Date)"
msgstr "moment (Date legacy)"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:162
msgid ""
"Native bindings via `perry-ext-moment` (v0.5.549). `moment` is in "
"maintenance mode upstream — prefer `dayjs` for new code, but Perry supports "
"both for existing codebases."
msgstr ""
"Binding nativi tramite `perry-ext-moment` (v0.5.549). `moment` è in modalità"
" di manutenzione upstream — preferisci `dayjs` per il nuovo codice, ma Perry"
" supporta entrambi per le codebase esistenti."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:166
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import moment from \"moment\";\n"
"\n"
"const m = moment().add(7, \"days\");\n"
"console.log(m.format());\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:173
msgid "rate-limiter-flexible"
msgstr "rate-limiter-flexible"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:175
msgid ""
"Native bindings via `perry-ext-ratelimit` (v0.5.552). In-memory limiter is "
"wired; Redis / cluster backing stores are follow-ups."
msgstr ""
"Binding nativi tramite `perry-ext-ratelimit` (v0.5.552). Il limiter in-"
"memory è collegato; i backing store Redis / cluster sono sviluppi futuri."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:178
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { RateLimiterMemory } from \"rate-limiter-flexible\";\n"
"\n"
"const limiter = new RateLimiterMemory({ points: 5, duration: 1 });\n"
"try {\n"
"  await limiter.consume(\"ip-1.2.3.4\");\n"
"} catch (rateLimitErr) {\n"
"  console.warn(\"blocked:\", rateLimitErr);\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:189
msgid "worker_threads"
msgstr "worker_threads"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:191
msgid ""
"Partially recognized at HIR-lowering time (`parentPort` / `Worker` shapes) "
"but full dispatch is incomplete. For data-parallel work today, prefer "
"`parallelMap` / `parallelFilter` / `spawn` from `perry/thread` (see "
"[Threading](../threading/overview.md))."
msgstr ""
"Parzialmente riconosciuto in fase di lowering HIR (strutture `parentPort` / "
"`Worker`), ma il dispatch completo è incompleto. Per il lavoro data-"
"parallel, preferisci oggi `parallelMap` / `parallelFilter` / `spawn` da "
"`perry/thread` (vedi [Threading](../threading/overview.md))."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:196
msgid ""
"```text\n"
"import { Worker, parentPort, workerData } from \"worker_threads\";\n"
"\n"
"if (parentPort) {\n"
"  // Worker thread\n"
"  const data = workerData;\n"
"  parentPort.postMessage({ result: data.value * 2 });\n"
"} else {\n"
"  // Main thread\n"
"  const worker = new Worker(\"./worker.ts\", {\n"
"    workerData: { value: 21 },\n"
"  });\n"
"  worker.on(\"message\", (msg) => {\n"
"    console.log(msg.result); // 42\n"
"  });\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:214
msgid "commander (CLI Parsing)"
msgstr "commander (parsing della CLI)"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:216
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { Command } from \"commander\"\n"
"\n"
"function commanderExample(): void {\n"
"    const program = new Command()\n"
"    program.name(\"my-cli\").version(\"1.0.0\").description(\"My CLI tool\")\n"
"\n"
"    program\n"
"        .command(\"serve\")\n"
"        .option(\"-p, --port <number>\", \"Port number\")\n"
"        .option(\"--verbose\", \"Verbose output\")\n"
"        .action((options: any) => {\n"
"            console.log(`Starting server on port ${options.port}`)\n"
"        })\n"
"\n"
"    program.parse(process.argv)\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:235
msgid "lru-cache"
msgstr "lru-cache"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:237
msgid ""
"The wired constructor takes the npm v7+ options-object shape (`new "
"LRUCache({ max: 100 })`) — the older positional form `new LRUCache(100)` "
"falls through to a `max=100` default."
msgstr ""
"Il costruttore cablato accetta la forma dell'oggetto opzioni di npm v7+ "
"(`new LRUCache({ max: 100 })`) — la forma posizionale più vecchia `new "
"LRUCache(100)` ricade sul valore predefinito `max=100`."

#: src/stdlib/other.md:241
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { LRUCache } from \"lru-cache\"\n"
"\n"
"function lruCacheExample(): void {\n"
"    const cache = new LRUCache({ max: 100 }) // max 100 entries\n"
"\n"
"    cache.set(\"key\", \"value\")\n"
"    console.log(cache.get(\"key\"))   // \"value\"\n"
"    console.log(cache.has(\"key\"))   // true\n"
"    cache.delete(\"key\")\n"
"    cache.clear()\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/other.md:255
msgid "child_process"
msgstr "child_process"

#: src/stdlib/other.md:257
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"import { spawnBackground, getProcessStatus, killProcess } from \"child_process\"\n"
"\n"
"function childProcessExample(): void {\n"
"    // Spawn a background process\n"
"    const { pid, handleId } = spawnBackground(\"sleep\", [\"10\"], \"/tmp/log.txt\")\n"
"\n"
"    // Check if it's still running\n"
"    const status = getProcessStatus(handleId)\n"
"    console.log(status.alive) // true\n"
"    console.log(`pid=${pid}`)\n"
"\n"
"    // Kill it\n"
"    killProcess(handleId)\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

